definition: lit. strung through and filled with evil (idiom); filled with extreme evil/replete with vice/guilty of monstrous crimes

sentences.english: That robber is laden with guilt.
The fool fills himself up with evil, even if collecting it just little by little.
sentences.chinese: 如同滴水能注滿水瓶，愚人累積小惡至罪惡滿盈。

sentences.english: My tears could not help coming.
The moon wax till it become full, and then wane.
sentences.chinese: 月亮漸漸變圓直至滿盈，然後再變虧缺。

sentences.english: Of rubies and diamonds, of silver and gold, His coffers are full, He has riches untold.
sentences.chinese: 白玉和碧翠鑽石和金銀，在父倉庫裏，積蓄豐富滿盈。

sentences.english: And you see tears fall, so the heart has been.
sentences.chinese: 與君一見淚滿盈，只因此心已洛印。

sentences.english: The moon rains out her beams, and heaven is overflowed.
sentences.chinese: 射出煙雨般的光柱，天際滿盈。

sentences.english: If you had infinite (free) time to yourself what are the three things you would do?
sentences.chinese: 要是有滿盈的時間讓自已支配，會做哪三件事？

sentences.english: People say orange is a lively, energetic color.
sentences.chinese: 人們說橙色是滿盈生機的主動向上的顏色。

sentences.english: Life is chock-full of fun! the key is tsimilarg the time to find it.
sentences.chinese: 生活中滿盈了快樂，關鍵是花些時間徐徐去發現快樂。
